        field_f = false;
        field_g = new String[][]{new String[]{"Using this on one of your minions will make it go faster for a while...a lot faster. Try it! Be aware that your zombie will also wander around a lot more if you're not paying attention.", "You can try to be <col=00ff00>annoying</col> with this by using it either on humans or enemy zombies."}, new String[]{"Using this on a minion will make it melt into a puddle of sticky goo that simply won't go away. Humans will be slowed down by it, but zombies are not affected.", "If you're feeling <col=00ff00>hostile</col> enough, you can melt enemy zombies, killing them. Nasty!"}, new String[]{"Apply this powerup to a zombie and it will produce a <col=ff0000>phantom copy</col> of itself. The phantom can't move, but will scare any humans that go near it.<br><br>Other overlords will be able to recognise the phantom for what it is, though...", "...unless you make it more <col=00ff00>realistic</col>. That will fool even enemy overlords into thinking it's a real zombie, and they might even waste one of their own powerups on it!"}, new String[]{"Using this powerup will <col=ff0000>disguise</col> one of your minions as a human. Even overlords will see that zombie as a human, too! The minion will be able to approach humans without scaring them away, and won't lunge until it's close enough for a kill.", "You can spend time to make the illusion more <col=00ff00>realistic</col>. This will still fool humans the same way, but your opponents will think that your minion is one of their own zombies. This is very useful for infiltrating enemy lines..."}, new String[]{"Blow them up! Yes, you can BLOW THEM UP! Try it - this will <col=ff0000>detonate</col> one of your zombies, <col=ff0000>stunning</col> everything around it. Only the zombie it was used on will be killed, but it's still very useful.", "It's even more useful if it's <col=00ff00>hostile</col>, though - in this case, you can target an enemy zombie.<br><br>Think about it. The little thing dies and it stuns all its friends nearby!", "Or, if you've developed <col=00ff00>lethal</col> modifiers, the resulting explosion will kill. Everything. Yes, it will kill anything around it."}, new String[]{"The <col=ff0000>screech</col> of a zombie is a horrible thing. Horrible, but useful... Its bloodcurdling sound will paralyse any humans within earshot of a screeching zombie. The screeching zombie cannot move while doing so, though.", "That is, unless you make the powerup a bit more <col=00ff00>mobile</col>... Who wouldn't find a mobile screeching zombie useful?", "Or you could focus on <col=00ff00>imposing</col> your will on your enemies, and make one of them screech."}, new String[]{"Hmm. This is interesting. Why do you have this?"}, new String[]{"<col=ff0000>Curse</col> the puny humans into joining your legions! Apply this to a human (within your range, of course) to convert it into one of your zombies.<br><br>Especially useful when done across a wall.", "<col=00ff00>Hostile</col> versions of this powerup turn even enemy zombies to your cause. Think about it - the enemy overlord is losing one and you're gaining one. Nothing wrong with that maths."}, new String[]{"Drop the <col=ff0000>hammer</col> on an enemy zombie or on a human to stun them. They will be dazed and unable to move for a while. It lasts longer on humans.", "<col=00ff00>Lethal</col> hammers can kill. You don't want to play around with those.<br><br>No, wait, yes you do."}, new String[]{"Poisonous <col=ff0000>miasma</col> is really useful. Choose a spot on the map and that area will be blocked off with an acidic cloud -- no zombies or humans will move there, or even see through it.<br><br>Try using it to block humans from running or to prevent an enemy zombie from reaching certain places."}, new String[]{"For every barrier along the way, there's a way to <col=ff0000>breach</col> it. Point to a place and the walls will become ethereal, allowing free passage to your zombies or giving an escape route to humans fleeing the enemy.<br><br>This will also clear miasma out. But watch out -- once the time is up, the walls will come back in and trap any zombies or humans in the way!"}, new String[]{"<col=ff0000>Haze</col> will pollute the view of other overlords, bugging their systems. It may cause optical illusions, but be warned: it will also affect you, albeit to a lesser extent."}, new String[]{"Particularly evil overlords are able to make the earth tremble and <col=ff0000>quake</col> with their technology. The screens of the other overlords will shake, hampering their targeting abilities. The effect on your screen, however, will be minimal."}, new String[]{"Engulf your opponents in flames with a <col=ff0000>fireball</col>. Although it will only stun, it's a versatile powerup that can be used anywhere within your area of influence.", "And a few particularly <col=00ff00>deadly</col> overlords can make it burn a target to cinders, killing instead of stunning. A wonderfully evil ability to have."}, new String[]{"Humans will run from any zombies that get close to them. But, if you make a zombie truly <col=ff0000>fearsome</col>, humans will ignore normal zombies and focus on getting away from what they see as the largest threat. The fools will run straight into your clutches!", "What's even better is that you can <col=00ff00>impose</col> it on your enemies, scaring away their prey before they can bite!"}, new String[]{"Bring the weight of their worries upon them and make them crawl... Attach these psychological <col=ff0000>shackles</col> to humans to reduce their speed for a while.", "Just because they're dumb, doesn't mean they can't be affected. Enemy zombies will also slow down when shackled if you're <col=00ff00>annoying</col> enough."}, new String[]{"Make one of your zombies <col=ff0000>charming</col> for a time with this powerup. It will attract humans with its newfound (and ephemeral) beauty, and will not lunge at them.<br><br>This only works as long as the humans are not already running away from a normal zombie, though.", "If it serves your evil purposes, you could always <col=00ff00>impose</col> this powerup on an enemy zombie."}, new String[]{"One of the most versatile powerups, this will allow you to foil an opponent's plans by <col=ff0000>countering</col> a powerup's effect.<br><br>Try using it on a disguised zombie, a meltdown puddle or an environmental effect from the Planetary research tree."}, new String[]{"Enable one of your zombies to <col=ff0000>teleport</col> itself to a different location by using this powerup. After using it on the zombie, give it a movement order and it will teleport to the designated spot!"}, new String[]{"Welcome to the test chamber. <col=00ff00>Select a powerup</col> below to learn more about it."}, new String[]{"Welcome to the test chamber. Since you're a <col=00ff00>Sceptic</col>, you won't be able to use any powerups... Except for <col=ff0000>counter</col>, of course."}, new String[]{"I see you have run out of zombies. Here are some more to toy with.", "Welcome, Overlord. You can move the camera by using the <col=ff0000>'W', 'A', 'S' and 'D' or the arrow keys</col>. You can also <col=ff0000>right-click and drag with your mouse</col>. Try this now.", "Also, you can zoom in and out of the map <col=ff0000>using your mouse's scroll wheel</col> or by <col=ff0000>holding the '+' or '-' keys</col>. Try that now.", "This is one of your zombies. <col=ff0000>Click on it to select it</col>.", "You can tell the zombie where to go by <col=ff0000>clicking on the map</col>. Zombies are slow to react, but they'll get there eventually.", "One zombie isn't a horde. <col=ff0000>Send your zombie to greet and eat that person over there.</col>", "Deselect your zombies by right-clicking on the map. Try that now.", "You can select multiple zombies by <col=ff0000>clicking and dragging a box around them</col>. You can also use <col=ff0000>'CTRL'-'A'</col> to select all your zombies at once. Do that now.", "This is your portal. Send zombies through it to score points. Humans are worth even more! <col=ff0000>Send someone through the portal now</col>.", "Powerups can help you hunt humans. You can learn more about powerups in your laboratory. <col=ff0000>Press 'Z' or click on the speed powerup icon below to activate it.</col>", "Great! Now use the powerup by <col=ff0000>clicking one of your zombies</col>. It will take a moment to be applied. You can only use powerups within a certain radius of your zombies and portal.", "The match is over when most of the humans are gone (or you're the only overlord left). Send your zombies through your portal to finish this tutorial and go to your lab."}};
